title: Jason Rao’s CV
text:
Computer Science Student

jasonrao@byui.edu | LinkedIn | GitHub



Pursuing a Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science with a minor in Data Science and Virtual Art.


Software development, data analysis, and web development.




Programming Languages: Python, C#, Java, JavaScript, HTML, CSS, SQL
Languages: Chinese, English, Spanish
Other: Leadership, management, teamwork, customer service





January 2023 - Present Brigham Young University - Idaho, Rexburg, ID
- Bachelor of Science in Computer Science
- Minor in Data Science, GPA: 4.0
January 2021 - December 2023 Brigham Young University - Hawaii, Laie, HI - Bachelor of Science in Computer Science
- Minor in Virtual Art and Entrepreneurship, GPA: 3.78



October 2023 – Present Customer Services Representative, Brigham Young University - Idaho, University Operations, Rexburg, ID
- Lead phone inquiries and build work orders to support university operations.
June 2022 – July 2023 Stage Manager, Brigham Young University Hawaii, McKay Auditorium
- Oversaw backstage operations during performances, ensuring technical elements run smoothly.
June 2022 – December 2022 Vice President of China Club, Brigham Young University - Hawaii, Laie, Hawaii
- Led a club of over 120 members, coordinating events and managing communications.
September 2021 - June 2022 Customer Services Representative, Brigham Young University - Hawaii, Facilities Management, Laie, Hawaii
- Managed incoming calls and created work orders to support university facilities operations.
September 2018 - June 2020 Yearbook Editor in Chair, Academia Juarez - High School, Chihuahua, Mexico
- Led a yearbook team of 12 to create a comprehensive annual publication showcasing school events and student life.



February 2022 Game (Hunter and Beast) - Java, OOP
January 2023 Digital ID - SDLC, Market Research
October 2024 Personal Website - HTML, CSS, JS
January 2024 Student Record System - Python, MySQL, Firebase
April 2024 Color To-Do - React Native, Firebase, AWS
